# Push after each build

After each build or set of code changes that are ready to deploy, **you must output the exact push sequence** so the user can run it in the Cursor terminal without asking.

Include these three blocks (with the actual files and commit message for this change):

```
git add <paths or .>
git commit -m "Short description of change"
git push origin main
```

Example: if you changed `src/app/page.tsx`, output:

```
git add src/app/page.tsx
git commit -m "Hero: graphic first, target above fold"
git push origin main
```

Do this at the end of your response whenever you have made changes that should be pushed. The user does not want to request the push each time.
